{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC20","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Meet WidgetKit"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10028-Meet-WidgetKit"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10028-meet-widgetkit"]}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10028","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (23 min)"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"abstract":[{"text":"Meet WidgetKit: the best way to bring your app’s most useful information directly to the home screen. We’ll show you what makes a great widget and take a look at WidgetKit’s features and functionality. Learn how to get started creating a widget, and find out how WidgetKit leverages the power of SwiftUI to provide a stateless experience. Discover how to harness your existing proactive technologies to make sure your widget surfaces relevant material. And create a Timeline that ensures your content is always fresh.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Where-we-can-find-the-new-widgets","type":"heading","text":"Where we can find the new widgets","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iPhone and iPad Home screens","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iPhone and iPad  Today view"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS Notification Center"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"What-Makes-A-Great-Widget","type":"heading","text":"What Makes A Great Widget","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Glanceable: great widgets display the right amount of content"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Relevant: great widgets display relevant content at the right place and time, this is very important for Smart Stack, too","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Personalized: great widgets allow configurations and support as many sizes as possible, widget configurations are done via intents","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Widget are not mini apps: think of the as your app content projection onto the homescreen"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"How-WidgetKit-Works","type":"heading","text":"How `WidgetKit` Works","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC20-10028-widget_works","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All widgets are built in SwiftUI","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WidgetKit"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions are background extensions that return a series of view hierarchies (a.k.a. views) in a "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/timeline","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Our widget extension donates this timeline (with our views) to the Home screen which will present them at the correct time according to the timeline."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This way there’s no app launch, load etc: the widgets are immediately glanceable","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Timelines can be refreshed from main app or via scheduled update from the extensions"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Defining-a-Widget","type":"heading","text":"Defining a Widget","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Main concepts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Kind (a custom "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":"): identifies the different widgets that we provide (for example we can have a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"detail"},{"type":"text","text":" widget display only one object, and a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"type":"text","text":" widget displaying multiple objects)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuration: Either "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/staticconfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (no user configuration) or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/intentconfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (allows user customization)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"| "},{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-10028-static_configuration"},{"type":"text","text":" | "},{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-10028-intent_configuration"},{"type":"text","text":" |"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/widgetfamily","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": a.k.a. the templates\/sizes a widget support: it can be any combination of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/widgetfamily\/systemsmall","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/widgetfamily\/systemmedium","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/widgetfamily\/systemlarge","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Placeholder: A temporary view WidgetKit uses to render the widget for the first time, generic representation of the widget (without any user data)","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC20-10028-placeholder","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-Glanceable-Experience","type":"heading","text":"Creating a Glanceable Experience","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Stateless UI","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"No scrolling","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No videos or animated images"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Easy tap interactions with deep link into our app","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Views-Timelines-and-Reloads","type":"heading","text":"Views, Timelines, and Reloads","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Three types of UI we should provide:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Placeholder","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/intenttimelineprovider\/snapshot(for:with:completion:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": when is where the system needs to quickly display a single entry, our extension should return it as quickly as possible"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Timelines: basically multiple snapshots combined with a date that tells the system at what time that view should be shown"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Reloads","type":"heading","text":"Reloads","level":4},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reloads happen when the system wake up the widget to ask for a new timeline for each widget displayed on the device."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reloads make sure that our widget content is always up-to-date for our user"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"TimelineProvider-Definition","type":"heading","text":"TimelineProvider Definition","level":3},{"code":["public protocol TimelineProvider {","    associatedType Entry: TimelineEntry","    typealias Context = TimelineProviderContext","","    func snapshot(with context: Self.Context, ","                    completion: @escaping (Self.Entry) -> ())","","    func timeline(with context: Self.Context, ","                    completion: @escaping (Timeline<Self.Entry>) -> ())","","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TimelineEntry"},{"text":": mainly a date.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Context","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": environment information for which the system is asking us for entries.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"snapshot function: the system is asking us for a single entry (to be returned as soon as possible)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Timeline function: the system is asking us for series of entries and attached reload policy (a.k.a. when we want the system to ask for a new timeline)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Timeline-Reload-policy","type":"heading","text":"Timeline Reload policy","level":4},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When our extension ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/timelineprovider","type":"reference"},{"text":" is asked to provide a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"code":"Timeline","type":"codeVoice"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/timeline","overridingTitle":"Timeline","type":"reference"},{"text":", we also need to define our reload policy:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"atEnd","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": tells ","type":"text"},{"code":"WidgetKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to request a new timeline only after the date of the last entry has passed","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after(date: Date)"},{"text":": tells ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WidgetKit"},{"text":" to request a new timeline only after a specified date","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": tells "},{"code":"WidgetKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to never request a new timeline, the app will let "},{"code":"WidgetKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" know when a new timeline is available"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Reloading-via-app","type":"heading","text":"Reloading via app","level":4},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We can ask the system to reload a specific widget or all widget kinds.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We can use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URLSession"},{"type":"text","text":" to kick off a task and use batch request as well background session to reload our widgets."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Personalization-and-Intelligence-Aspects","type":"heading","text":"Personalization and Intelligence Aspects","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Driven by two major contexts:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Intents: used as a mechanism to allow users to configure our widget","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Relevance: which allows us to inform the intelligence in the widget stack."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Intents are powered by the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit"},{"type":"text","text":", the same used with Siri and Shortcuts"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The widget relevance is particularly useful when the user has multiple widgets into a smart stack: the stack will be sorted based on each entry ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/timelineentryrelevance","type":"reference"},{"text":", duration, and more","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Written-By","type":"heading","text":"Written By","level":2},{"numberOfColumns":5,"columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"abadikaka","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":1},{"content":[{"anchor":"Michael-Abadi-Santoso","type":"heading","text":"Michael Abadi Santoso","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/abadikaka","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributed Notes"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/abadikaka","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/michaelabadi.com","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/x.com\/michaelabadiii","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}